# Unreal Companion - Windsurf Rules

## Project Context

MCP server for Unreal Engine 5.7+. Python (FastMCP) + C++ Plugin architecture.

## Key Files

- `AGENTS.md` - Project knowledge base
- `Python/tools/` - MCP tool implementations (62 tools)
- `Plugins/UnrealCompanion/` - C++ plugin

## Python Tool Guidelines

For `@mcp.tool()` decorated functions:

- No `Any`, `object`, `Optional[T]`, `Union[T]` types
- Use `x: T = None` for optional params (not `x: T | None = None`)
- Include docstrings with Args, Returns, Example

## Unreal Engine 5.7

- Z-up, left-handed coordinate system
- Units: cm, kg, degrees
- Axes: X=Red (forward), Y=Green (right), Z=Blue (up)

## Tool Naming

```
Python function = C++ command = MCP tool name
Format: category_action (snake_case)
```

## Batch Operations

All batch tools support:
- `on_error`: "rollback", "continue", "stop"
- `dry_run`: Validate without executing
- `auto_compile`: Auto-compile (default: true)

## Common Paths

```
/Game/Blueprints/    # Blueprints
/Game/Materials/     # Materials
/Game/UI/            # Widgets
```
